comments:
During the training phase, I noticed that the words were paired - each set of two words would start with the same two symbols and diverge on the third. As soon as I started to associate the first two symbols with their pairs, I would simply look at the third symbol to determine the correct word its respective pair.

The actual exercise, after the training phase, threw me off because the symbols would come and go in an instant, and would show up on different parts of the screen. I quickly noticed the first two symbols, but would sometimes struggle to see the third, depending on the timing.

All in all, it was a pretty interesting study.
